# Aurora — Cursor rules (legacy single-file)
#
# When working on a feature in this repo, route your work through the
# five-agent pipeline defined in AGENTS.md. Each role has strict rules
# in .claude/agents/<role>.md. Shared state lives in
# .aurora-pipeline/work/<TICKET-ID>/feature_context.json.
#
# Per-stage rules also live in .cursor/rules/*.mdc; this single-file
# version is here only for older Cursor versions that do not read .mdc.

# ALWAYS read AGENTS.md before doing any meaningful work.
# - The 5 roles (Product Owner → Architect → Engineer → SDET → Reviewer) are
#   sequential and non-skippable.
# - Each role owns specific fields in feature_context.json and may not touch
#   fields owned by another role.

# ENGINEERING RULES (from ai/guidelines/*.md, enforced for ALL roles):
# - TypeScript strict, no `any`, no `console.log` left in.
# - Layering: routes -> controller -> service -> repository -> Prisma.
#   Controllers MUST NOT touch Prisma.
# - Money is stored as Int cents.
# - Validation: Zod on every body/query/param. Schemas live in packages/shared.
# - Errors: throw AppError, never try/catch in controllers, never
#   res.status(...).json({...}) for errors.
# - Named exports only for React components.
# - Cookie-based JWT auth; argon2 for passwords.
# - Tests: Vitest + supertest for backend, Playwright POM for UI E2E.
# - No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.

# WHEN ASKED TO BUILD A FEATURE:
# 1. Look at .aurora-pipeline/work/<TICKET-ID>/feature_context.json.
# 2. Identify which stage the ticket is currently in (status field).
# 3. Act ONLY as the role that owns that stage. Do not try to be a
#    one-shot generalist.
# 4. Reference the role's full spec at .claude/agents/<role>.md.
# 5. Update feature_context.json per the role's output protocol.

# ALWAYS PREFER to use the Claude Code slash commands if available:
# /feature-init, /feature-triage, /feature-design, /feature-build,
# /feature-test, /feature-review, /feature-pipeline.
